Furthermore, the differentiation between liquid and powder forms of amino acid biostimulants highlights the importance of convenience, storage, and ease of use for farmers. Liquid formulations are favored for their quick absorption and application, making them suitable for foliar spraying and rapid nutrient uptake by plants. On the other hand, powder forms are valued for their longer shelf life and storage convenience, appealing to users looking for cost-effective solutions that can be stored for extended periods without compromising efficacy.

